To enable Emmet in HTML files in VS Code, you don't need to do anything special as Emmet support is built-in for HTML by default. Emmet abbreviations are automatically listed along with other suggestions and snippets in the editor's auto-completion list when working with HTML files [DOC-doc_5a813444_5].

If you want to customize Emmet behavior or use it in other languages, you can use the `emmet.includeLanguages` setting to map other languages to HTML. For example, to use Emmet HTML abbreviations inside JavaScript, you can add the following to your settings:

```json
{
    "emmet.includeLanguages": {
        "javascript": "html"
    }
}
```

This setting allows you to associate one of the Emmet modes (such as `html`) with other languages [DOC-doc_6b1ef6e0_9].
